entries.notit_1: This isn't the disc I hired you to bring me.
entries.npc_smuggle_1: I did what he asked me to. He'll square my debts now, right?
entries.dontknowyou_1: I'm waiting to meet somebody else.
entries.otherescort_1: I'm not the person you need to meet.
entries.npc_failure_1: The terrain was a little too rough for you, I guess.
entries.npc_noloc_1: My slicer is a little wary of strangers right now, so I'll have to call him and smooth your arrival. Check with me in a minute.
entries.npc_work_1: Why haven't you got that information for me yet?
entries.npc_reward_1: All right. You can be sure I'll send this record of criminal activity where it can do the most good. You've helped me a lot, and I won't forget it.
entries.npc_backtowork_1: I've told you all I can. Are you still going?
entries.npc_4_1: My boss has been altering shipping orders to cover up bribes he's been accepting. I want you to pick up the original records from my data slicer. What do you say?
entries.npc_3_1: I guess I was wrong about you being able to handle yourself.
entries.npc_2_1: My slicer has a bit of a gambling problem, so he's hiding outside the city at the moment. I'll let him know you're picking up the data.
entries.npc_1_1: I work for the Corporate Sector Authority. You look like you know how to handle yourself. I need someone to pick up a disc from a data slicer. Do you want to make a few credits?
entries.npc_reset: Not quite up to the task yet? See me again when you can handle it.
entries.cantwork: I need your undivided attention. When you've finished your current job, I might be able to find some work for you.
entries.next: I don't have anything for you at the moment. Try me again later.
